{
  "text": "Vol. 2, No.6, 2008 respectively. In these figures, a horizontal axis represents the ratio of two fluids depth β and a vertical axis indicates the total fluid height h (1) + h [CITATION_1] . In Fig.3 , function Ω varies from 0.63 to 0.70. As seen in Fig.4 , Ω is distributed between 1.16 and 3.00. In these figures, there are no parameters which satisfy Eq.(31). Thus, the resonance caused by 3WRI does not occur in the case of Table 2 (A) and (B).",
